This paper deals with value function approximation in reinforcement learning, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of high-dimensional representations and matrix-based learning algorithms suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on sketching as a method for improving computational efficiency suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of neural networks and other function approximators suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
